Identify the stylopharyngeus muscle passing between the superior and middle constrictor muscles on each side. Identify the glossopharyngeal nerve following the stylopharyngeus muscle into the gap between the superior and middle constrictor muscles.
Other than the stylopharyngeus, ALL muscles of the pharynx (the three constrictors, the palatopharyngeus and the salpingopharyngeus) are innervated by the vagus nerve.
In addition, the vagus nerve innervates the levator veli palatini and the palatoglossus.
